annotation.TEXT: My basic shurikens can 2-shot Blooper. I wonder what the power level of these shurikens and that powered-up sword I had a moment ago are?
Uh, oh. That's right. There's bullet cannons in this corridor. Fortunately, the 3-way missiles are capable of destroying Bullet Bills. Still, this could be tricky.
There's a power up here. No, I don't want the laser, not when I already have this AWESOME SPREAD GUN!
Alright, now for A-1 Steak Sauce, I think I'll go with someone who hasn't seen action in a while... Samus!
I may want to get my homing missiles ready for something up ahead. Also, since I have the ability to, I'm going to climb on the ceiling here!
Yep, there's the warp zone to world C. However, I'm of course not going to take it. I just wanted to show that it was there.
Also, unlike all of the other sky bonus areas (except 9-3's), this one doesn't end with a row of 3 coins in the ending pit.
I think that power up was the Ice Beam, which I do not want.
And so, the fraction of The Lost Levels that I've now completed is 10/13.
DOUBLE KILL!
Well, let's see if the randomly selected Shadow can do better. There is one bit of good news though-- I'm now back up to 50 NP. (I was at only 7 NP before that death.)
Awesome combo! (8 hits) 1-life combo!
There's a vine leading to a sky bonus area, but I'm gonna break these bricks first.
Alright, I'll collect it now!
Maybe I won't have to use the 3-ways if I'm careful, though.
Now, unfortunately, by going over the flagpole, I've forfeited the ability to get 5000 from it. But, I think I might be able to get 800 if I jump from the edge of the flagpole's base block.
Ha. Hammer Bros. fall down the hole.

Now, I think there's only one thing this star is really useful for, and that's this Hammer Bro. over here, which I guess isn't a big deal for a Contra guy, but for a plumber that lacks fireballs, it's pretty useful.
Aw, what? I couldn't 1-shot a Blooper with that powered-up sword?
Oh, man. He's really crowding me, and there's not really a lot of room to back up...
Alright, so which of these characters should I use for world B? Place your votes now!
There's a 1-up in the ceiling brick directly above the springboard here.
Oh, nuts! I forgot about these bullet cannons! They aren't a big deal for a plumber, but for a Contra guy that lacks fireballs, they could be big trouble!
Alright, it's boss time!
I probably could've bomb jumped up to the coins that I missed in that area, but that would've been very time-consuming.
Alright, first let's get rid of this kooper, and then let's see if I can go over the flagpole!
Whoa, Bowser flame.
Alright, that's about enough brick-breaking for now. Let's go and finish this level.
Nuts! I was really hoping to hit at least one Podoboo with that shell... Well, maybe I'll try again in an "and a half" bonus episode.
Note: B-2 is a water level, but that doesn't necessarily mean that you absolutely have to pick a swimmer for that level...
Aw, the victory music that I used when I got that obnoxious trinket in VVVVVV's Golden Spiral got cut off there. Oh, well. Now, for A-3, I'll use a random Ryu.
Oh, wait, what? Can I... not reach the warp zone area with Lance?
Okay, I'm very close to the goal now. I've just gotta get these koopers outta the way first!
Perfect. One homing missile was exactly enough to stun that koopa without killing it.
To be continued... Yo!
That was a kind of risky missile pickup to go for, but whatever.
Alright, I'll just show you the gist of this room and hurry on out of here. Note that the power up (and poison) along with the upper 6 coins are unreachable if you can't break bricks.
I don't want to recklessly break all these bricks, because this pipe up here leads to a bonus room! ...Uh, oh! Time limit!
Watch out for the evil mushroom here.
Excellent!
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! Up above are the voting results like always.
Okay, looks like I got past them without any problems.
...Snake? ...Snake! ...SNAAAAAKE!!!
Splut!
Aww... That sucks... Well, it's not like I was planning on actually warping anyway, but I was at least gonna show it off.
...Okay, they're flying Medusa Heads in this case. That's just as bad!

Oh, that was fun, and there's still more, but I want to be more careful around here. There's a star in one of the lower bricks here, and I don't want to reveal it too soon before I'm ready to collect it.

What the french toast?! I totally hit the jump button there, well before Ryu walked off the clouds to his doom, but it didn't register for some reason! (I'm pretty sure I wasn't late with the jump button press, but unfortunately, I have no proof.)
Oh, man. So many bricks to destroy! SO MUCH DESTRUCTION!!! MWAHAHAHA!!!
I've stopped firing for a moment so that I can concentrate on not screwing up these jumps. (So, I guess I'm not gonna break every single brick in this level.)
Got him!
Okay, that hidden mushroom was right where I remembered it would be, so that's good.
Break 'em all!
There was an alt. skin vote for the Tetrimino (Sophia III). In addition, Ryu's vote was for A-3, so I'll use him there.
Demo count: 9
Up next, I think I'll go with the AWESOME SPREAD GUN for A-2, since it's an underground level with lots of bricks for me to destroy!

Also, there was a vote to release Torchic and get an Azumarill with Thick Fat and a Slaking with Minus, and there was a vote for me to play Cave Story. Sorry, but I doubt I'll be making any Cave Story vids.
Whoops. Hit the missile button by accident there. That's okay. I've still got 50 left.
...As soon as I can remember which one of these guys is Ryu... LOL. Okay, there he is.
Yep, 800. Alright, A-3 is now complete!
Don't need it. I'm maxed out.
At least I'm having good luck so far with the flying... whatever these fish that have beaks are called.
There's another power up, and for the third time in a row, it's the Ice Beam. I guess I must have everything else that Samus can possibly get if I'm only being offered the Ice Beam now.
Shut up, clock. The goal's right there.
Oh, sweet! I actually pulled off the whole 1-up combo with this slow character!
There's another evil mushroom, and more Hammer Bros., which I can easily shoot down with my AWESOME WAVE BEAM! ...Nah, it's not quite on the same level as AWESOME SPREAD GUN.
Remember: Red parakoopas in this game behave like green koopas when they lose their wings, in that they don't turn around at edges of ledges. (This is true in the original SMB games as well.)
Almost forgot about those hidden coin blocks.
And we're done with A-2. Shame I didn't get to show off the warp to world B. Maybe I'll make a bonus "and a half" episode just to show it. What do you guys think?
I got a Bean of some sort this time.
Looks like I got one of the regular Ryus this time. Okay, now A-3 is a cloud level that I believe has flying cheepos!
Whoa. That could've been bad. I forgot that shells often like to skip over single-tile gaps in Crossover.
Nice. Now that I'm over the flagpole, there's something that I want to show off over here...

One thing I often loved to do at this level's start here in All-Stars was get myself bouncing repeatedly off of the two red koopas within this structure. If I did it just right, I could get awesome 1-up combos!
Alright, let's see how well I can do here... Unfortunately, the coins start off really high in the sky bonus areas of worlds A-D. Also, the moving platform is now shorter than usual.
Aw, too bad I'm not using a fast character here, because a 1-up combo is possible here. Well, let's see how well Samus can do...
Alright, well I'm unable to show it here, but there is a warp zone to world B further to the right here.
Well, that's interesting. It's not quite a Tetrimino, but I did end up with Sophia III!
Now, I know there was that Tetrimino vote, but Random got 2 votes, so I definitely have to go with Random at least once in this episode!
